The paper focuses on traffic engineering in Software Defined Networks (SDN), which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.AL (Algorithms). The paper also mentions scalability, which could indicate cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with dynamic traffic, which could suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
